# Project Timeline (13-15 Weeks)

## Weeks 1–2: Core Setup & Movement
- Set up Unity project and Git repository
- Implement top-down player movement (WASD / arrow keys)
- Configure key bindings
- Add camera follow system
- Create basic tilemap with collision
- Deliverable: Player can move around a playable map

## Weeks 3–4: Combat Basics
- Implement real-time combat system
- Add melee attack (sword/axe)
- Add magic attack (staff projectile)
- Implement health and damage system
- Create first enemy type (melee chaser)
- Deliverable: Player can fight and defeat enemies

## Weeks 5–6: Weapons & Enemy Variety
- Implement weapon switching (keys 1 / 2)
- Add second enemy type (ranged enemy)
- Implement basic enemy AI (detect, chase, attack)
- Deliverable: Combat variety with multiple weapons and enemies

## Weeks 7–8: Inventory & Loot
- Implement simple list-based inventory
- Add breakable crates with health
- Implement loot drop system
- Add item pickup and usage (healing potions)
- Deliverable: Full loot and inventory loop

## Weeks 9–10: Boss & Game Completion
- Implement boss enemy with special attacks
- Add win condition after boss defeat
- Polish combat and balance difficulty
- Deliverable: Game has a clear ending

## Weeks 11–12: Optional Features (Stretch Goals)
- Add customization options
- Add dialogue or small story elements
- Add additional enemies or map areas (if stable)
- Deliverable: Optional enhancements without affecting core gameplay

## Week 13: Testing & Finalization
- Bug fixing and playtesting
- Review AI-assisted code and tests
- Resolve merge conflicts and stabilize main branch
- Final documentation and presentation
- Deliverable: Stable, playable demo
